<p>I'm an algorithm developer and data analyst, working with startups and SMEs, after I graduated last year from my Computational Physics PhD.  I research, design, prototype and implement algorithms for novel applications.  I also enjoy using computational mathematics and insights from data to solve business problems, and to help businesses make better decisions.</p>

<a class="btn" href="portfolio.html">
    <button class="btn btn-primary" style="
       margin-top: 15px;
       margin-bottom: 15px;
    ">View my portfolio</button>
</a>

<p>I have 4 years Python experience and 12 months consulting experience, providing data analysis, algorithm design and visualisations.  My skills include statistical data analysis, MySQL, Google Analytics, Google Maps, GIS, web scraping, Cython and C++.  I have experience with algorithm development, using tree solutions to solve fantasy sports problems, designing a geographical carpooling algorithm and building grid-based differential equation solvers for computational Plasma Physics.  I am currently improving my machine learning and d3 skills.</p>

<p>I have a PhD in Computational Physics from Imperial College London, have published academic papers and given presentations at international conferences.</p>

<p>My most recent major project was working with Lineup Lab for 5 months, <a href="lineuplab.html">designing and implementing an algorithm for optimising fantasy sports</a>.  Below is an example visualisation of a <i>tree</i>, the type of solution used.</p>

